and porting it to the Mac or vice versa

00:23:38.509 --> 00:23:41.750
and what do you do about Linux and so forth.

00:23:41.750 --> 00:23:44.000
You have WebKit as the platform.

00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:45.730
Your deployment is simpler.

00:23:45.730 --> 00:23:46.630
It's a patching.

00:23:46.630 --> 00:23:52.880
You have a web server anyway, and so these
hybrids create a really interesting scenario

00:23:52.880 --> 00:23:59.280
where they have a desktop experience
with a web app development ease,

00:23:59.279 --> 00:24:05.639
and so this allows you to get greater developer
productivity, and your hosting services already exist.

00:24:05.640 --> 00:24:10.750
You already have an Apache server, a MySQL,
more than likely in your enterprise anyway,

00:24:10.750 --> 00:24:13.869
and so you're leveraging your existing infrastructure.

