Now, what does this do to, for
example, your infrastructure costs,

00:37:13.070 --> 00:37:16.910
in terms of the number of people that
you need to support your business?

00:37:20.880 --> 00:37:22.780
So, this is actually Apple.

00:37:22.780 --> 00:37:24.890
We've taken to this to an extreme.

00:37:24.889 --> 00:37:27.609
We have nobody to administer your desktop systems.

00:37:27.610 --> 00:37:31.170
We're all responsible for administering our own systems,

00:37:31.170 --> 00:37:35.430
to keep our software up to date, and
to install packages that we need.

00:37:35.429 --> 00:37:44.500
So, we have moved the IT focus in Apple away from
the desktop, back to the centralized services.

00:37:44.500 --> 00:37:47.570
This allows us to do some really
interesting things, which is,

00:37:47.570 --> 00:37:51.670
as well as needing fewer people to
do this, we can actually consolidate.

00:37:51.670 --> 00:37:57.470
You do things like consolidation of fragmented
services, because we're now focusing on the core.

00:37:57.469 --> 00:38:03.669
So, for example, Apple used to have 5 different HR
databases that needed all sorts of maintenance and support.

00:38:03.670 --> 00:38:11.320
